      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ITS CONFIDENTIAL (11) showed strong form against the top three-year-olds at the end of his last campaign, highlighted by his Vicbred Super Series Final win. Has to overcome the outside draw but he is unbeaten in four fresh attempts and should be ready to go again off a trial placing. SAO PAULO SIMBA (10) was 5.5m off ITS CONFIDENTIAL in the Vicbred final when last seen in November but earlier won a heat and placed in a semi-final of that series. Won the last two times he raced here. Draws out but has strong fresh record and was readied with two nice trials. PARTY CENTRAL NZ (2) jumps in grade off his easy last-start win at this venue but he draws better and has plenty of upside. INTRUSION (9) brings good form from Victoria having won his last two outings at Melton, one of them from a similar barrier to this. JETTER SON (5) looks close to a win following back-to-back placings here and is suited up to this distance having recorded a win and a placing from two attempts.",
